VERSION 1
WHEN PRESENT \bdelete\s+\b(?:[^\s]+)\b
WHEN EXPR MISSING:=\s*nullptr|=\s*NULL|std::unique_ptr|std::shared_ptr|std::weak_ptr
REPORT AS area_of_interest
REASON Detects use of `delete` without setting the pointer to `nullptr`, which can result in dangling pointers.
TRACE Externalized rule logic for Dangling Pointer: delete without nullptr.
